"Every device connected to the internet leaves a trace. This tool reads it."

A Python command-line tool that retrieves detailed geographic and network information for any IP address using the ip-api.com API.
Features

Detects country, region, and city
Displays ISP and network provider info
Returns precise coordinates (latitude & longitude)
Fast results directly in your terminal

        Requirements
Python 3.8+
requests library



             Installation
git clone https://github.com/norby90/ip-locator.git
cd ip-locator
python3 ip-locator.py



          Usage
bashpython main.py 8.8.8.8
Example Output
IP Address  : 8.8.8.8
Country     : United States
Region      : California
City        : Mountain View
ISP         : Google LLC
Latitude    : 37.4056
Longitude   : 122.0775

  
  API
Uses ip-api.com free tier — 45 requests/minute, no API key required.


